  "text": "We see in Table 2 that applying suspected-spam removal (SpamRm) upon the initial ranking improves performance (except for MAP for ClueWeb-09). This finding is in line with previous reports [CITATION_1] . We also see that ReRank improves over SpamRm in a majority of the relevant comparisons; for MAP, the improvements are often statistically significant. In the few cases ReRank is outperformed by SpamRm, the differences are not statistically significant. Filter, on the other hand, is outperformed by SpamRm in many cases.",
